  "texts": [
    "In experts' opinions, the question of who should decide on the (ethical) acceptability of AI's development remains open and requires public discussion.",
    "Considering stakeholders' requirementsAI experts questioned whether AI focuses on the needs of those impacted by its usage.",
    "Regarding patient care, a few experts expressed how AI may not be genuinely patient-centric as patients' views may be systematically omitted from AI's development (Table 4).A participant [Rn41 (MEAI)] described how AI's development might be marketing-driven rather than oriented toward patients' needs.",
    "A few experts brought bioethical principles of justice and fairness into the discussion and how important it is to consider the distribution of benefits for patients and doctors.",
    "A lingering question is whether AI solves the challenges patients and doctors face, or if it focuses on the goals of the technology industry."
